The paper proposes a novel approach to Multiple Instance Learning in neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically mentions computer vision, medical image processing, and bioinformatics as fields where MIL problems arise frequently, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.BIO are likely sub-categories. The proposed approach involves a bag-level ranking loss function that can be applied to any neural architecture, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions testing the approach on convolutional neural networks, which suggests that cs.NE is a possible sub-category as well.
